      "name": "Mesh independence study — pressure head and shear stress convergence",
      "description": "Three mesh densities (3.2 M, 6.8 M, 14.1 M cells) evaluated for the FDA centrifugal pump geometry. Grid convergence index (GCI) computed for pressure head and volume-averaged shear stress at the 3.5 L/min / 3500 RPM operating point. GCI < 2.1% on fine grid accepted as sufficient discretization convergence."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-02-flow-rate-validation",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Flow rate and pressure head validation against FDA experimental data",
      "description": "Simulated pressure-flow curves compared against published FDA benchmark experimental data across 5 operating points. Mean absolute error in pressure head: 4.3%. No uncertainty bands on experimental measurements were reported in the source dataset; consequently no uncertainty characterization was incorporated into this validation result. Agreement deemed acceptable for MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-03-hemolysis-index",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index comparison against predicate device measurements",
      "description": "Computed normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values converted to relative hemolysis index (RH) and compared against predicate device in vitro measurements at matched operating conditions. RH < 1 at all five operating points confirms worst-case condition identification. Experimental scatter in predicate measurements not formally propagated through model comparison."
    }
